    "updated_at": "2017-02-14T17:58:55Z",
    "body": "Hey @kevinsawicki, I can't find any chrome plugin APIs for getting power events, only ones to [prevent the machine/screen from sleeping](https://developer.chrome.com/apps/power).\r\n\r\nWhat do you think a good next step would be in narrowing this down?\r\n\r\n# Some relevant links\r\n\r\n- [Electron Power Monitor Source](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/atom/browser/api/atom_api_power_monitor.cc)\r\n- [Chromium power_monitor.h](https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/power_monitor/power_monitor.h?q=base/power_monitor/power_monitor+package:%5Echromium$&l=1)\r\n- [Chromium power event dispatch](https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/power_monitor/power_monitor_source.cc?l=47)\r\n- [No apparent Chromium Bugs](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/list?can=2&q=PowerEvent&colspec=ID+Pri+M+Stars+ReleaseBlock+Component+Status+Owner+Summary+OS+Modified&x=m&y=releaseblock&cells=ids) mentioning `PowerEvent`\r\n"
  },
