    "updated_at": "2017-05-09T19:18:12Z",
    "body": "I've run into this same issue on a Microsoft Surface Pro 4 running the latest Windows 10 (as of this writing) and Electron v1.6.5.  The 'on-ac' and 'on-battery' events do work as expected, but the 'suspend' and 'resume' events don't fire.\r\n\r\nI'm curious if anyone has a workaround for this issue.  I might end up using electron-edge and write a solution in C# for now, but I was hoping to avoid that."
